link:
Popsicles DRIVEBY: August 28, 2020 between 2:00 PM-3:00 PM.

A CCA Tradition is being altered, but it's definitely not lost! In August we usually have Popsicles on the Playground coupled with Open House. This year, our plans have changed just a bit. Our teachers are super excited to meet their new students and get them pumped up about the school year! We hope you join us for this special event. Here's how it will work:
‚óè Drive through the serpentine, single file, on August 28 between 2:00 PM-3:00 PM.
‚óè All of our CCA teachers will be lined up, by grade level with a posterboard introducing themselves. They will be waving "hello" as you drive past!
‚óè As you prepare to exit the lot, our fabulous Administrative Team will be distributing popsicles to each vehicle.

We hope you join us for the Popsicles Driveby so you can meet your child‚Äôs teachers and enjoy a cool treat.

Canton Charter will be opening in person for the 2020-21 school year on September 8, 2020 using a Hybrid Learning Model. This will include a combination of in-person and remote instruction. Each student will be provided access to a Chromebook if they need one to complete at-home learning.

Hybrid Learning
Students spend two days learning in-person at school and three days learning virtually at home.
Students will be organized into groups: Group A and Group B. Families will be grouped together.
This shifts attendance so that approximately only 50% of our students will be in-person on the same day, allowing us to implement safety guidelines.
When in-person, students will receive‚Ä¶

>>>>>>> master
School of Excellence (We got 5 stars!)
AQM Award (We have an AQM of 93!)
Only schools with an AQM of 90 or higher were recognized. AQM, or Academic Quality Measure, is a general measure of our previous year performance on state tests compared to other schools in a similar FRL cohort; 2/3 based on growth and 1/3 based on proficiency.
Congratulations, Canton!

post_text:
Homemade Playdough Receipe:
>>>>>>> master

Materials:
3 cups of flour
1 ¬Ω cups of salt
6 tspn cream of tartar
3 tbspn of oil
3 cups of water

Instructions:
Dissolve salt in the water.
Pour all ingredients into a large pot.
Stir constantly over medium heat until a ball forms by pulling away from the sides.
Knead the dough mixture until the texture matches playdough (1-2 minutes).
Store in plastic container. Should last for at least 3 months.
You can even try adding a package of Kool Aid to give the playdough color and a nice scent!
text:
Homemade Playdough Receipe:

Materials:
3 cups of flour
1 ¬Ω cups of salt
6 tspn cream of tartar
3 tbspn of oil
3 cups of water

Instructions:
Dissolve salt in the water.
Pour all ingredients into a large pot.
Stir constantly over medium heat until a ball forms by pulling away from the sides.
Knead the dough mixture until the texture matches playdough (1-2 minutes).
Store in plastic container. Should last for at least 3 months.
You can even try adding a package of Kool Aid to give the playdough color and a nice scent!

Hi- my name is Gloria Jarvis and I graduated from Canton Charter Academy in 2016. I am collecting board games, cards, and puzzles for families in the Wayne-Westland Community Schools during this time of shut down. Families in the shelter cannot leave their rooms due to the virus leaving them with not much to do. I would like to collect games or puzzles that families have outgrown or don't use anymore. Please donate games that are in good condition and have all their pieces. You can reply to this post or through Facebook messenger. I can pick it up from your house or you can drop it at mine. Thank you!

post_text:
Today is National Kindergarten Day!

The first kindergarten (which means garden for the children) was developed in Blankenburg, Germany, in 1837. Each year on April 21st, National Kindergarten Day honors the birthday of the man who started the first Kindergarten. Friedrich Wilhelm August Frobel (April 21, 1782 ‚Äì June 21, 1852) is credited with starting the very first Kindergarten in Germany in 1837.
Help us celebrate this day by sharing your favorite Kindergarten experience in the comments below!

text: April 6-10 is Spring Break! We encourage you to take a break from learning and enjoy your family. Our CCA staff will be doing this as well. Be safe!

post_text: Compassion is our moral focus for the month of April and there certainly is an opportunity to display compassion during this time. Stated simply, compassion means showing care or concern for others. If you can remember back to an opening ceremony in November, Mrs. Titus challenged each of us to be kind to others, especially when we are feeling down or worried, and then we will feel better as well. We would like to extend this challenge to you again as we are all saddened by the closure, but certainly necessary for safety. Whether you make a phone call to someone you love, write a letter to a friend, share good news with your teacher or even give your sibling a hug, you will find yourself feeling a little happier. Keep looking for the positive. We miss you all!

post_text:
NHA Students Show Compassion
>>>>>>> master

After earning $100 for jumping in a pool of icy water, Amaya decided to use half of her money to buy school supplies for children who may not have them at home. She and her sister, Arya, both attendees of Plymouth Scholars, made academic ‚Äúgoodie bags‚Äù. These bags were filled with pencils, erasers, paper, and more. These bags are at Canton Charter Academy, under the awning, on the wooden bench. The girls want each family to know, ‚ÄúIf you need materials, come and get them.‚Äù

We are thankful to have students like Amaya and Arya who are showing compassion for others during this difficult time.

If your family is in need of supplies, please drop by Canton Charter Academy and take what you need.
text:
NHA Students Show Compassion

After earning $100 for jumping in a pool of icy water, Amaya decided to use half of her money to buy school supplies for children who may not have them at home. She and her sister, Arya, both attendees of Plymouth Scholars, made academic ‚Äúgoodie bags‚Äù. These bags were filled with pencils, erasers, paper, and more. These bags are at Canton Charter Academy, under the awning, on the wooden bench. The girls want each family to know, ‚ÄúIf you need materials, come and get them.‚Äù

We are thankful to have students like Amaya and Arya who are showing compassion for others during this difficult time.

If your family is in need of supplies, please drop by Canton Charter Academy and take what you need.
